cs.LG, cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.CL 

The paper presents a clustering algorithm that uses deep autoencoders for nonlinear dimensionality reduction and clustering jointly. This approach is relevant to several subfields of computer science, including machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), artificial intelligence (cs.AI), neural networks (cs.NE), and natural language processing (cs.CL). However, since the paper focuses on clustering high-dimensional datasets, we can expect that the most likely sub-categories are those related to machine learning, computer vision, and artificial intelligence.
